cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SE

The paper discusses the design and effectiveness of online help systems for software intended for the general public, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR) aspects. The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing (cs.CL) and contextual help (cs.CY) in improving online help systems. Additionally, the paper touches upon software engineering (cs.SE) aspects in terms of designing effective online help systems.
